 	<li>Writing Tools</li><br/>
 	<li><a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/visual-intelligence/">Visual Intelligence</a></li><br/>
 	<li>ChatGPT integration</li><br/>
</ul><br/>
After delaying the personalized &zwnj;Apple Intelligence&zwnj; &zwnj;Siri&zwnj; features, Apple took down its &zwnj;Apple Intelligence&zwnj; ads that had <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/03/10/apple-pulls-iphone-16-ad-more-personal-siri/">highlighted the functionality</a>. Apple originally published ads with unavailable &zwnj;Siri&zwnj; features when the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-16/">iPhone 16</a> launched, and now it's <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/03/20/apple-intelligence-siri-lawsuit/">facing lawsuits as a result</a> from customers who expected the &zwnj;Siri&zwnj; features on their new &zwnj;iPhone 16&zwnj; devices.<div class="linkback">Tags: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/apple-ads/">Apple Ads</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/apple-intelligence/">Apple Intelligence</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/05/02/apple-intelligence-features-ad-2/">Available Apple Intelligence Features Highlighted in New Ad</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/available-apple-intelligence-features-highlighted-in-new-ad.2456400/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>